! Inline formatting

''bold'' text, //italic// text, __underline__ text, ~~strikethrough~~ text.

Super^^script^^ and sub,,script,, and ``inline code`` and @@highlighted@@.

Combined: ''//bold italic//'' and //''italic bold''// and ``//literal slashes//``.

!! Styled inline spans

@@.tc-big-green-button A styled span with a class@@
@@color:red;A span with an inline CSS colour@@
@@background-color:yellow;color:black;Multiple CSS declarations@@
@@color:blue;.myclass CSS and class together (styles must come before classes)@@

!! Dashes and special characters

Dashes: an en-dash -- and an em-dash --- in text.

HTML entities: &amp; &copy; &mdash; &rarr; &#x2192; &#160; &nbsp;.

!! Showing literal characters

TiddlyWiki has no backslash-escape: a `\` is a literal character, so `\''`
still starts bold and `` \` `` still starts inline code. To show wiki characters
literally, use inline code or HTML entities instead:

* Literal markup via inline code: `''not bold''` and `//not italic//`.
* Literal characters via entities: &#47;&#47; (two slashes), &#38; (ampersand),
  &lbrace;&lbrace; (two braces).

!! Inline code variants

Single backtick `code`, and double backtick to embed a literal backtick:
``code with ` backtick inside``

!! Mixed line

A mix on one line: ''bold //and italic// together'' with `code`, a
[[WikiLink]], an external https://tiddlywiki.com link, a <<currentTiddler>>
variable, a {{SomeTiddler}} transclusion and a `<$text text="widget"/>`.
